data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction code won't compile. Replace it with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action`-based API means you can use normal C# control flow — no more `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` plumbing.

---

### 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full paths

Two changes combine here:

- **Duplicate property names** across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) get a numeric suffix appended automatically.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate column-rename migrations. **Fix:** pin the original names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, preserve old column names:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your logger won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way. `logCommandText` contains constant-redacted SQL safe for logging; use `command.CommandText` for the actual SQL.
